NAME:
   ssm - Secure Shell Manager

USAGE:
   ssm [--options] [tag]
   example: ssm --show --exit vpn
   example: ssm -se vpn

VERSION:
   0.4.0

DESCRIPTION:
   ssm is a connection manager designed to help organize servers, connect, filter, tag, and much more from a simple terminal interface. It works on top of installed command-line programs and does not require any setup on remote systems.

AUTHOR:
   "Leonardo Faoro" <me@leonardofaoro.com>

GLOBAL OPTIONS:
   --show, -s                  always show config params (default: false) [$SSM_SHOW]
   --exit, -e                  exit after connection (default: false) [$SSM_EXIT]
   --order, -o                 show hosts with a tag first (default: false) [$SSM_ORDER]
   --config string, -c string  custom ssh config file path [$SSM_SSH_CONFIG_PATH]
   --theme string, -t string   define a color theme (default: sky|matrix) [$SSM_THEME]
   --debug, -d                 enable debug mode with verbose logging (default: false) [$SSM_DEBUG]
   --help, -h                  show help
   --version, -v               print the version

COPYRIGHT:
   (c) Leonardo Faoro & authors
